Unideb Run - Endless Runner Game

Unideb Run is a fast-paced endless runner where the player controls a character running through a 3D environment inspired by the University of Debrecen. The goal is to survive as long as possible while avoiding obstacles and achieving the highest score.

Gameplay

The character runs automatically.

The player must avoid obstacles by moving, jumping, or sliding.

The score increases based on distance traveled and collectibles.

If the player hits an obstacle, the game ends.

The player can restart to try again and beat their previous score.

Features

Endless gameplay

Increasing difficulty

Simple and responsive controls

Randomized or procedural obstacles

Score and high-score tracking

Basic animations and sound effects

Clean and simple user interface

Controls

(Adjust based on your game)
A or D / Left or Right Arrow - Move
Space - Jump
S - Slide
ESC - Pause

How to Play

Start the game from the main menu.

Avoid obstacles by using the movement controls.

Stay alive as long as possible.

When you collide with an obstacle, the game ends.

Restart and try to set a new high score.

Tools Used

Unity - Game engine
C# - Scripting language
Blender - 3D modeling
Affinity Designer - UI and graphic design
Visual Studio Code - Code editor

How to Open the Project

Clone or download the project folder.

Open it in Unity (use the recommended version).

Open the main scene.

Press Play to test the game.

Project Status

The game is still being improved. Future updates may include:

New obstacles

Better animations

UI improvements

Performance optimizations
